    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="640"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2991</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 10.50 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s August 5.<note n="1" xml:id="d640fn1">Not printed.</note> Agreement
                    to give free transit to American tobacco paid for August 4 construed by Foreign
                    Office to mean paid for by European importer. This decision injuriously affects
                    shippers who bought for export to selves or European buying houses which they
                    control. These interests urgently desire broader construction of expression
                    “paid for,” especially as to goods afloat.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRP1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
